&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Onboarding Specialist (Remote — Global)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Aktos&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Aktos builds software for debt collection agencies — modern, all-in-one tools that help agencies manage accounts, communicate with debtors, and get paid faster. We’re a fast-growing startup building the next generation of collection technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring an &lt;strong&gt;Onboarding Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to own complex, multi-month customer implementations from kickoff to go-live. This role is project-management heavy: you’ll derisk programs, coordinate stakeholders across functions, manage timelines and dependencies, and ensure clients successfully adopt Aktos.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own 3+ month onboarding programs end-to-end — create and run project plans, track milestones, and remove blockers to keep implementations on time&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead stakeholder management — map sponsors, align cross-functional stakeholders, run steering calls, and negotiate scope/timing tradeoffs&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively derisk implementations — maintain risk registers, define gating criteria, escalate appropriately, and keep executive stakeholders informed&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose technical and product blockers — analyze data mismatches, product configuration gaps, integration issues, and propose pragmatic fixes&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product &amp;amp; engineering — surface recurring issues, document patterns, and recommend product improvements to reduce future onboarding effort&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize and scale onboarding — create playbooks, runbooks, templates, and internal documentation to speed up future implementations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly with clients — set expectations, guide them through setup, and resolve questions efficiently&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Bonus) Perform light technical work — data imports, SQL lookups, API checks, test configurations, and validation of integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who this role is for (Ideal backgrounds)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re explicitly looking for people who have &lt;em&gt;led long, complex onboarding programs (3+ months)&lt;/em&gt; where project management, stakeholder management, and derisking were the day-to-day work. Typical backgrounds we love include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementation/Professional Services at an &lt;strong&gt;enterprise SaaS&lt;/strong&gt; vendor (ERP, CRM, HRIS, billing/collections) — titles like &lt;em&gt;Implementation Manager&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Senior Onboarding Specialist&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Professional Services Consultant&lt;/em&gt;, or &lt;em&gt;Technical Project Manager (Onboarding)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Success/Onboarding leads at companies that deliver &lt;strong&gt;3–6 month&lt;/strong&gt; deployments (examples: NetSuite, Salesforce, Workday, Oracle NetSuite, Zendesk/Support Enterprise, HubSpot Enterprise)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project managers or consultants who managed customer rollouts at payroll/benefits, billing platforms, or other regulated vertical SaaS with complex integrations and data migrations&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People from consulting practices or systems integrators who ran scoping, SOWs, and cross-functional delivery for multi-stakeholder clients&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
